t/sig1.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Condescending apologies suck</span><hr size=1> Mmmmmm... all these devils now. I just LOVE playing with the devil!<br>
<br>
When I first started playing EQ, I was told over in Oasis that Lockjaw was a FFA mob. I didn't know what that meant. I was told to just fight him with everyone else and hope you get the kill for his uber loot. That was 3 years ago with my first character in her young teens. It didn't take long to find out (and thankfully without me actually KS'ing someone on a so-called FFA mob) that the info I had been given was wrong. I can somewhat accept this kind of behavior from someone brand new to the game figuring they are like I was: misinformed. But you would think by the time you hit your 30's, much less 50's, that you'd know not to do that.<br>
<br>
Yes, the KS and/or ninja was bad. The gloating of it was bad. The taunting of other people here that rightfully pointed out the err of Fab's ways has been bad. But the so-called apology just plain sucks. It reminds me of someone else I tend to harrass when I see 'em fucking up... shallow apologies with a disclaimer of &quot;I did nothing different from what others have done in the past&quot; just doesn't qualify as an apology. Once again we have someone diverting the truth away from them while totally lacking in the ability to admit they were wrong and unwilling to quit looking at others to justify their own behavior.<br>
<br>
I don't know you as far as having chatted with you goes. But I do think I know enough from your posts here to be able to know all I need to know. <br>
<br>
Those that think guild tags and reps don't go hand-in-hand are dead wrong! I won't hesitate to remove someone from my guild if they go against our charter and what we believe in. I will hesitate not only in letting someone with a questionable rep in joining the guild, but also in my groups. I know I am not alone in this attitude and practice either.<br>
<br>
For those that argue its just a game: its NOT! I really am an Iksar monk, a wood elf druid and rogue, a high elf chanter, mage, and cleric, a barbarian shaman, a gnome wizard, a dwarf, etc.<br>
<br>
Ok, I digressed a bit. Now its time to find the devil to play with! /who devil all <p><BR>
